<div class="answercell post-layout--right">
    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>To turn runtime value to compile value, I tend to use <a href="https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/utility/variant.html" rel="noreferrer"><code>std::variant</code></a> of <a href="https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/types/integral_constant" rel="noreferrer"><code>std::integral_constant</code></a> and then use <a href="https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/utility/variant/visit2.html" rel="noreferrer"><code>std::visit</code></a>:</p>
<pre class="lang-cpp s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-cpp"><span class="hljs-keyword">using</span> ColorVariant = std::variant&lt;
    std::integral_constant&lt;Color, Color::Red&gt;,
    std::integral_constant&lt;Color, Color::Green&gt;,
    std::integral_constant&lt;Color, Color::Blue&gt;
&gt;;

<span class="hljs-function">ColorVariant <span class="hljs-title">ToColorVariant</span><span class="hljs-params">(Color color)</span>
</span>{
    <span class="hljs-keyword">switch</span> (color) {
        <span class="hljs-keyword">case</span> Color::Red: <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> std::integral_constant&lt;Color, Color::Red&gt;{};
        <span class="hljs-keyword">case</span> Color::Green: <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> std::integral_constant&lt;Color, Color::Green&gt;{};
        <span class="hljs-keyword">case</span> Color::Blue: <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> std::integral_constant&lt;Color, Color::Blue&gt;{};
    }
    <span class="hljs-keyword">throw</span> std::<span class="hljs-built_in">runtime_error</span>(<span class="hljs-string">"Unsupported enum value"</span>);
}

<span class="hljs-comment">// Similarly for other enums</span>
</code></pre>
<p>and then</p>
<pre class="lang-cpp s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-cpp"><span class="hljs-keyword">template</span> &lt;<span class="hljs-keyword">typename</span> Func&gt;
<span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">constexpr</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">auto</span> <span class="hljs-title">perform</span><span class="hljs-params">(<span class="hljs-type">const</span> Vehicle&amp; vehicle, Func&amp;&amp; func)</span>
</span>{
    <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> std::<span class="hljs-built_in">visit</span>([](<span class="hljs-keyword">auto</span> color, <span class="hljs-keyword">auto</span> type) {
        <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> func.<span class="hljs-keyword">template</span> <span class="hljs-built_in">operator</span>()&lt;<span class="hljs-built_in">color</span>(), <span class="hljs-built_in">type</span>()&gt;();
    }, <span class="hljs-built_in">ToColorVariant</span>(vehicle.color), <span class="hljs-built_in">ToTypeVariant</span>(vehicle.type));
}
</code></pre>
<p>To avoid <code>func.template operator()&lt;color(), type()&gt;()</code> notation,
I tend to expect lambda of the form <code>[]&lt;Color color, Type type&gt;(std::integral_constant&lt;Color, color&gt;, std::integral_constant&lt;Type, type&gt;){/*...*/}</code> (with deducible type) (which might even be written as <code>[](auto color, auto type) {/*...*/}</code>), instead of <code>[]&lt;Color color, Type type&gt;(){/*...*/}</code></p>
    </div>
    <div class="mt24">
        <div class="d-flex fw-wrap ai-start jc-end gs8 gsy">
            <time itemprop="dateCreated" datetime="2025-05-27 12:25:57Z"/>
            <div class="flex--item mr16" style="flex: 1 1 100px;">
                


<div class="js-post-menu pt2" data-post-id="79640480" data-post-type-id="2">

